Peter Mertens, Sushila Maan, Carrie Batten, Narender Maan, Kyriaki
Nomikou, Anna Sanders, Philip Mellor and Chris Oura (From the
Arbovirus Research Group and Bluetongue Community Reference
Laboratory, Institute for Animal Health, Pirbright Laboratory, Surrey
UK)

Christiaan Potgieter and Truuske Gerdes (Virology Division,
Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute, 100 Old Soutpan Road,
Onderstepoort, South Africa)

Piet Van Rijn, Rene van Gennip, Yvon Geurts, Daniel Veldman, Jan
Boonstra, (Central Veterinary Institute of Wageningen UR (CVI)
Department of Virology, P.O. Box 65, 8200 AB Lelystad, The
Netherlands Houtribweg 39, 8221 RA Lelystad, The Netherlands

References
----------
1. Batten CA, et al: A European field strain of bluetongue virus
derived from two parental vaccine strains by genome segment
reassortment. Virus Res. 2008 Oct; 137(1): 56-63
(<http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18598726>).
2. Maan S, et al: Sequence analysis of bluetongue virus serotype 8
from the Netherlands 2006 and comparison to other European strains.
Virology. 2008 Aug 1; 377(2): 308-18
(<http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18570969>).
3. Mertens PP, et al: Design of primers and use of RT-PCR assays for
typing European bluetongue virus isolates: differentiation of field
and vaccine strains. J Gen Virol. 2007 Oct; 88(Pt 10): 2811-23
(<http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17872535>).
4. Shaw AE, et al: Development and initial evaluation of a real-time
RT-PCR assay to detect bluetongue virus genome segment 1. J Virol
Methods. 2007 Nov; 145(2): 115-26
(<http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17586061>).

