[We are most indebted to Prof Mertens and his colleagues at the IAH,
Pirbright, at Lelystad (the Netherlands), and at Onderstepoort (South
Africa) for the detailed report above and the comprehensive
assessment of the situation. The virology is excellent and the
conclusions are carefully worded.

It will be critical to learn what the complete sequencing of genome
of this new outbreak strain reveals; that is, whether there is a
complete match with the vaccine strain or whether it contains genome
subunits from another strain. If it turns out to be a reassortant
this will suggest that the strain has been present for some time
undetected, and the identity of any non-BTV-6 subunits may allow
tracking of the origin of this strain.

According to the official notification of the Dutch authorities to
the OIE (World Organisation for Animal Health), this outbreak started
on 10 Sep 2008. - Mods.AS/CP]
